14. Interview Questions

Q. What are Digit Separators?

Answer

Digit Separators are a C++14 feature that allows single quotes (') inside numeric literals to 
improve readability. The compiler ignores these separators during compilation.

-----------------------------------------

Q. Which character is used?

Answer

Single quote (')

Example

1'000'000

-----------------------------------------

Q. Does the separator affect the value?

Answer

No.

Example

1000000

and

1'000'000

represent exactly the same integer value.

-----------------------------------------

Q. Does it increase memory usage?

Answer

No.

The separator exists only in the source code and is ignored by the compiler.

-----------------------------------------

Q. Can Digit Separators be used in binary literals?

Answer

Yes.

Example

